definitions.definition: Free from writing, printing, or marks; having an empty space to be filled in.
Lacking characteristics which give variety; uniform .
examples: a blank desert; a blank wall; blank unconsciousness
Not a cloud in the blank blue sky.

definitions.definition: Abject; absolute; complete; downright ; sheer; utter.
examples: There was a look of blank terror on his face.

definitions.definition: Without expression , usually because of incomprehension .
examples: Failing to understand the question, he gave me a blank stare.

definitions.definition: Empty; void ; without result; fruitless ; futile .
Devoid of thoughts , memory , or inspiration .
examples: The shock left his memory blank .

definitions.definition: Of ammunition : having propellant but no bullets ; unbulleted .
examples: The recruits were issued blank rounds for a training exercise.

main_definition: ( archaic ) White or pale ; without colour .
